# 🎯 Hands-On Lab Outcome

By completing this lab, you practiced:

---

## ✔ Linux User Management

### Create Users
```bash
sudo adduser dev1
sudo adduser qa1
sudo adduser intern1
```

### Verify Users
```bash
cat /etc/passwd
id dev1
```

---

## ✔ Group-based Access Control

### Create Group
```bash
sudo groupadd projectteam
```

### Add Users to Group
```bash
sudo usermod -aG projectteam dev1
sudo usermod -aG projectteam qa1
```

### Verify Group Membership
```bash
groups dev1
groups qa1
```

---

## ✔ Real-world Project Directory Management

### Create Project Structure
```bash
sudo mkdir -p /projects/ecommerce-app/logs
sudo mkdir -p /projects/ecommerce-app/releases
```

### Verify Directory Structure
```bash
tree /projects
```

---

## ✔ Deployment User Configuration

### Create Deployment User
```bash
sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash deployuser
```

### Grant Sudo Access
```bash
sudo usermod -aG sudo deployuser
```

### Verify User Details
```bash
id deployuser
```

---

## ✔ Secure Permissions Setup

### Assign Ownership
```bash
sudo chown -R :projectteam /projects/ecommerce-app
```

### Set Secure Permissions
```bash
sudo chmod -R 775 /projects/ecommerce-app
```

### Verify Permissions
```bash
ls -ld /projects/ecommerce-app
```

---

## ✔ Production-style Deployment Simulation

### Switch User
```bash
su dev1
```

### Create Release File
```bash
touch /projects/ecommerce-app/releases/v1-release.txt
```

### Write Deployment Logs
```bash
echo "Deployment Successful" >> /projects/ecommerce-app/logs/deploy.log
```

### Verify Deployment Files
```bash
cat /projects/ecommerce-app/logs/deploy.log
```

